25|$|Expenses {{incurred}} in a trading, business, rental, {{or other}} income producing activity are generally deductible, though {{there may be}} limitations on some types of expenses or activities. Business expenses include all manner of costs {{for the benefit of}} the activity. An allowance (as a <b>capital</b> <b>allowance</b> or depreciation deduction) is nearly always allowed for recovery of costs of assets used in the activity. Rules on capital allowances vary widely, and often permit recovery of costs more quickly than ratably over the life of the asset.|$|E
