50|$|<b>Capital</b> <b>allowances</b> are the sums {{of money}} a UK {{business}} can deduct from the overall corporate or income tax on its profits. These sums derive from certain purchases or investments, outlined in the <b>Capital</b> <b>Allowances</b> Act 2001.|$|R
