50|$|<b>Capital</b> <b>allowance</b> reliefs can be {{set against}} the client’s taxable profits {{reducing}} the amount payable. Companies pay Corporation Tax at 20% or 26% (2011-12 figure), whilst individuals pay tax at 20%, 40% or 45%. Please note as it is an allowance against taxable profit, {{you have to be}} a tax payer to benefit, therefore this does not normally apply to property owned in SIPPS or by charities and trusts. Allowances are generated when a business client builds or acquires commercial property. The amount of plant contained within the building or acquired property is the key to maximising the relief.|$|E
